1
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:07,000
AI agents move real money on-chain — and they get drained. EIV keeps them honest, deterministically.

2
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:12,200
The user signs an authorization in plain language; GLM-5.1 turns it into a strict spec. The signature is the only source of truth.

3
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:16,000
Act 1. The agent is instructed to approve an unlimited allowance.

4
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:20,000
But GLM-5.1 reads the signed mandate and adjusts to a bounded approval on its own — the signature wins over the instruction.

5
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:26,000
Act 2. A prompt injection tries to redirect the output to an attacker. The agent refuses it on its own.

6
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:30,000
Act 3. Now the agent is fully compromised and submits the drain directly.

7
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:33,200
EIV rejects it deterministically — it never trusts the model.

8
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:39,800
Every verdict is attestable on-chain. A real attestation is live on Sepolia via ERC-8004.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:46,000
The model proposes. EIV decides. Deterministic, reproducible, zero dependencies.
